segments.text: It's hard.
The other thing, and I know you've run out of time.
And you've answered this also, in a way.
Please put yourself in George Mitchell's mind and tell us why he keeps you around.
What is it you do for him?
Why is he attracted to you?
What role?
Do you play for him, in terms of what's going on with him?
What goes on in his mind is a very good question.
I think part of his attraction to me is
I am an academic.
My background, I have a PhD from the University of Chicago, and I think that's impressive.
Two, there have been several occasions where things, where potentially very embarrassing things occurred, and he was able to call upon me.
I think that he, and I think also that he thinks that I add a dimension that is important to the Wimbledon Corporation.
That because of my background and my interests, and the fact that I'm not part of
You know, I'm not here with my eye on becoming the president of the Women's Corporation or doing Mike Richman's job.
And I don't know anything about energy and I care less about real estate.
I'm not...
So you're a detached observer and a participant?
Well, yeah.
And, you know, I take care of that and I take care of this and I take care of that.
And I guess that's...
I don't know any other reason really.
But he has, he surrounds himself with a lot of people like that.
And that seems to be one of his unique talents.
You know, the diversity of people in this community area is really interesting.
Yeah.
Because it is very unusual.
And they are really diverse and are alike quite often.
I try to explain to people, they say, well, why don't you call it a research park?
Why don't you call it a research forest or an industrial park?
And the point is, there isn't anything else like it in the country.
Yeah.
I mean, aside from the fact there's
venture capital, the ability to invest in some of these companies.
This whole community, in a sense, is dedicated to maximizing the success of companies in that bio-med and bio-tech.
You know, there are good schools here.
The scientists can jump on their bike.
If they want to come out at 2 o'clock in the morning, they can.
And we're able to offer a total package.
We've got a Japanese company that's interested.
And they said, well, what would it take?
And they said, look, education is very important to us.
We know you have good schools, but our kids go to the Japanese Juku Saturday school, supplementary school.
Well, that's way over in West Houston.
But we wanted very much for that company to be here.
So we proposed very simply, we'll provide a van Saturday morning.
We'll take the kids and bring them back.
And once we get a nucleus, we'll start our own supplementary school.
They're not in a lot of places.
No, we don't respond like that.
So anyway, I hope this has been helpful.
That's been very useful.
Yeah, I appreciate it all.
